Definition: an abnormal condition in which cerebrospinal fluid collects in the ventricles of the brain
Example: in infants it can cause abnormally rapid growth of the head and bulging fontanelles and a small face; in adults the symptoms are primarily neurological
Synonyms: adj, pert, hydrocephalic, hydrocephaly, abnormality, an, abnormal, condition, in, which, cerebrospinal, fluid, collects, the, ventricles, of, brain, infants, it, can, cause, abnormally, rapid, growth, head, and, bulging, fontanelles, a, small, face, adults, symptoms, are, primarily, neurological
Category: noun.state
